      "description": "Available is a driver-focused 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the iconic S54 3.2L inline-six powerplant. This high-revving engine utilizes individual throttle bodies and double VANOS variable valve timing to deliver a linear power band up to its 8,000 RPM redline. Power is sent to the rear wheels via a desirable Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a factory M-Variable limited-slip differential. This example has undergone essential preventative maintenance, including rear subframe reinforcement and a comprehensive VANOS overhaul to ensure mechanical longevity. The suspension retains its factory-tuned damping characteristics, providing the precise turn-in and chassis feedback expected of the M-division. While the exterior shows honest signs of enthusiast use, the drivetrain and structural integrity remain excellent for the purist seeking a mechanically sound icon.",
